def_en: If you look through a group of things, you examine each one so that you can find or choose the one that you want.
If you look through something that has been written or printed, you read it.

def_cn: （因生气、沉思等）对…视而不见
def_en: If you say that someone looks through another person, you mean that they look at that person without seeming to see them or recognize them, for example because they are angry with them or are thinking deeply about something else.
